cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.HC, cs.NE 

This paper is primarily focused on computer vision and machine learning techniques for facial expression recognition, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) sub-category. The paper also involves the use of manifold modeling and statistical analysis, which are common techniques in the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category. Additionally, the paper deals with human-computer interaction and emotion recognition, which could place it in the cs.MM (Multimedia) or cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) sub-categories. Finally, the paper involves the use of discriminant embedding, which is a technique commonly used in the cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) sub-category.
